










 








TEAM — SOMAVAC Medical Solutions, Inc
















































































Advancing Technology. Advancing Care.




TEAM
Our mission is to improve at home recovery after major surgeries by creating patient centered medical devices.

















































Our team is passionate about transforming the lives of people who struggle with the current post-surgical drains. After years of basic and engineering science research, we decided to start Somavac Medical because we wanted to help patients now and we got impatient with the slow pace at which scientific research typically moves. After witnessing the experience of people who live with JP drains, we felt compelled to create a solution that has the potential to profoundly help people. Esra Roan, PhD - CO-FOUNDER/CEO







Esra is the co-founder of Somavac Medical Solutions and an Associate Professor in Biomedical Engineering at the University of Memphis. Esra's more than 15 years of experience in product development and biomedical research gives her the tools to enhance the lives of patients with products that make a difference.  Her education is in Mechanical Engineering (TTU and U of Cincinnati). LinkedIN, GoogleScholar.Please contact Esra @ esra@somavac.com with any questions or comments.Josh Herwig - CO-FOUNDER/CTOJosh is a serial tinkerer with professional experience in machine design, electronics, and manufacturing. He holds a B.S. in Mechanical Engineering from Tennessee Technological University, and will be a summer 2016 graduate of the University of Memphis/UTHSC joint Master’s program in Biomedical Engineering.  Josh serves as the Chief Technology Officer for Somavac Medical Solutions, and is spearheading the device development.You can reach Josh at josh@somavac.com.







 Kaitlin Ganavazos, Engineering Intern







Kaitlin is an outstanding senior Biomedical Engineering student at the University of Memphis.  She joined SOMAVAC's team in June 2017 to take on a variety of supporting roles.  Besides pursuing an engineering degree, she is also an accomplished cellist. We appreciate her contributions already and happy to have her on our team.





 


 




























*Not yet FDA cleared or for sale in the U.S. Our device is patent pending.esra@somavac.com   josh@somavac.comSOMAVAC Medical Solutions, 20 S. Dudley St, Memphis, TN 38103, UNITED STATESJosh and Esra's photo is courtesy of Lauren Ready - Forever Ready Productions, LLC 



 







